# Lua Coding Style Guidelines

## Indentation and Formatting
- Use **two-space indentation** for all Lua files
- Set `tabstop`, `shiftwidth`, and `softtabstop` to 2
- Avoid hard tabs completely
- Use `stylua` for automatic formatting via none-ls and LSP

## String Conventions
- Prefer **double-quoted strings** over single quotes
- Use trailing commas in tables for cleaner diffs
- Match existing plugin specs formatting style

## Code Organization
- Keep feature-specific logic out of baseline files ([set.lua](mdc:lua/set.lua) and [remap.lua](mdc:lua/remap.lua))
- Expose helper modules under `lua/` with concise names
- Scope plugin-specific utilities near their specs
- Limit global namespace pollution

## Plugin Configuration
- Each plugin file should return a Lazy configuration table
- Use descriptive names for plugin files (lowercase, hyphenated)
- Follow existing patterns in [lua/plugins/](mdc:lua/plugins/) directory